TY  - JOUR
T1  - Evaluating Financial Risk in the Medicare Prospective Payment System
AU  - Dada, Maqbool
AU  - White, William D.
Y1  - 1999/03/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.45.3.316
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.45.3.316
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 316
EP  - 329
VL  - 45
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The Medicare Prospective Payment System (PPS) is analogous to an insurance scheme in which financial risk is mitigated through experience rating. In addition, risk is also mitigated through reinsurance provisions. Although a provider may not want this reinsurance, participation is mandatory. We develop a framework for evaluating financial risk under the PPS. We use this framework to examine optional reinsurance as an alternative risk mitigation mechanism. We illustrate an application of optional reinsurance using data for Medicare psychiatric inpatient services. Our analysis indicates that viable schemes exist for implementing optional reinsurance as a prospective payment option.
AB  - The Medicare Prospective Payment System (PPS) is analogous to an insurance scheme in which financial risk is mitigated through experience rating. In addition, risk is also mitigated through reinsurance provisions. Although a provider may not want this reinsurance, participation is mandatory. We develop a framework for evaluating financial risk under the PPS. We use this framework to examine optional reinsurance as an alternative risk mitigation mechanism. We illustrate an application of optional reinsurance using data for Medicare psychiatric inpatient services. Our analysis indicates that viable schemes exist for implementing optional reinsurance as a prospective payment option.
