TY  - JOUR
T1  - A “Parallel Approach” Path to Estimating Collision Risk During Simultaneous Landings
AU  - Barnett, Arnold
Y1  - 1999/03/01
PY  - 1999
DA  - 1999/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.45.3.382
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.45.3.382
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 382
EP  - 394
VL  - 45
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Airport capacity could increase if, even during inclement weather, independent landings could occur on parallel runways only about half a mile apart. A key question about such operations is whether the collision risk they entail is acceptably low. Pursuing that issue, we explore a method for estimating the chance that a plane on final approach during instrument flight conditions will ?blunder? in a way that could imperil nearby aircraft. We argue that the method could yield an attractive combination of high estimation accuracy and relatively low cost.
